                  PROREP REPORT SPECIFICATIONS




     1.  *TITLE

          Up to 3 lines, 80 characters each.  No  title  need  be
     specified.   One  or  more  blank title lines (followed by a
     non-blank title line) will be interpreted as blank titles.


     2.  *COLUMNS

          Up to 52 columns, 10 characters each.   The  number  of
     column headings supplied determines the number of columns or
     "periods"  in  the  analysis.   Blank  column  headings  are
     permitted  in  all  but  the  last column.  There must be at
     least one column defined.

          The column heading can be followed by  any  of  several
     options,  enclosed  in  angle  brackets  <>.  Column options
     override row options if both are  in  effect  for  the  same
     output field.  Column options include:

      DECIMALS = N to specify the number of decimal places to  be
               shown.   "N" can range from 0-8.  If no DEC = N is
               supplied, 2 decimal places are  shown.   A  number
               too  large  to  be  shown will be output as "***".
               (DEC = -1 will show up to  5  significant  digits.
               Numbers  to  large  to  fit into the output report
               will be shown in "E" format instead of "***".)

          NULL to null out each number in a column if  its  value
               is zero.

             $ to precede each value in the column with a  dollar
               sign.

             % to follow each value in the column with a  percent
               sign.

             ( to specify that any negative values in the  column
               should be displayed enclosed in parentheses rather
               than with a leading minus sign.

         COMMA to specify  that  commas  should  be  included  in
               output quantites to designate thousands, millions,
               etc.

          The six options may appear in any  logical  combination
     and  in  any  sequence, separated by commas or blanks.  They
     are specified anywhere  on  the  same  line  as  the  column

