                       PROREP FILE LAYOUT





          The file produced by PROREP is free format and  can  be
     created  by  the  experienced user through a standard system
     editor.  The file can contain line numbers.   However,  line
     numbers  will  not be saved if the file is edited or created
     via PROREP.  The following rules  should  be  followed  when
     editing a PROREP file outside PROREP.


             - The file must start each section with one  of  the
               keywords 
                         *TITLE 
                         *COLUMNS 
                         *ROWS 
                         *OUTPUT

               While the sections can be in any  order  (and  any
               one  section  need  not  be  contiguous), the very
               first line of the file must be a keyword.

             - Any   blank   lines   will   be   interpreted   as
               significant, i.e., as a blank column heading, etc.

             - Standard system protection codes can  be  used  to
               protect files as necessary.

             - Any input line can be continued onto another  line
               by including an "&" at the end of the line.

             - If line numbers exist, the first  character  after
               the line number will be ignored.

          Each report specification is on  the  file  as  entered
     through PROREP (although some respacing may occur to improve
     readability).   Thus,  the  PROREP  program  can  serve   to
     introduce  this  specification  structure  to  the new user.
     When the user becomes familiar with the file layout, he  may
     choose to create and edit his report files outside PROREP.

