          (1) SUBROUTINE  SETUP:  This  subroutine  contains  all
     statements which initialize report lines, or other variables
     at the start of a forecast.  An example might be a statement
     setting  a  "TOTAL  MARKET" report line variable equal to an
     initial starting level as specified by a "1971 MARKET"  data
     variable.  The SETUP subroutine would appear as follows:

   * any I/O from within the user's SETUP and  RULES  subroutines
     is subject to the following constraints:

            1. Only one logical unit open at a time.  Release the
               unit between IFILE and OFILE operations.

            2. Any logical unit opened  by  the  user  should  be
               released prior to returning to PROFILE control.

